  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "If Viber on your PC is not connecting to the internet or allowing you to reply to messages, there could be several potential issues. Here are some troubleshooting steps you can try to resolve the problem:\n\n1. **Check Internet Connection**: Ensure that your PC is connected to the internet and that the connection is stable. Try opening a web browser and accessing a few websites to confirm.\n\n2. **Restart Viber**: Close Viber completely and then reopen it. You can also try logging out and back into your account to see if that resolves the issue.\n\n3. **Restart Your Computer**: Sometimes, simply restarting your computer can resolve connectivity issues.\n\n4. **Update Viber**: Ensure that you are using the latest version of Viber. Check for updates in the app or download the latest version from the official Viber website.\n\n5. **Firewall and Antivirus Settings**: Your firewall or antivirus software might be blocking Viber. Check your firewall or antivirus settings and make sure Viber is allowed to access the internet.\n\n6. **Check Proxy Settings**: If you're using a proxy server, make sure that the settings are correct and that the proxy server is working as expected.\n\n7. **Network Configuration**: If you are on a work or public network, there may be network restrictions or configurations that are affecting Viber. Consider trying a different network if possible.\n\n8. **Reinstall Viber**: If none of the above steps work, try uninstalling Viber and then reinstalling it. This can sometimes fix underlying issues with the application.\n\n9. **Check Viber\u2019s Status**: Occasionally, there might be server-side issues with Viber that could cause connectivity problems. Check Viber's official social media channels or website to see if there are any known issues.\n\n10. **Contact Support**: If the problem persists, consider reaching out to Viber support for further assistance. They may be able to provide more specific troubleshooting steps based on your system and situation.\n\nBy going through these steps, you should be able to identify and resolve the issue with Viber not connecting properly on your PC.",
